---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About Us — NetSpeed Internet Telemetry & Diagnostics"
  description="Learn about the design, methodology, and engineering behind NetSpeed. Our speed test engine provides uncompromised telemetry via optimal server selection."
>
  <main class="flex-1 py-16 px-4 md:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-12">
      {/* Hero Header Block */}
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 border-b border-hairline pb-8">
        <span
          class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-mute block"
        >
          Our Mission
        </span>
        <h1
          class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-semibold tracking-tighter text-ink font-sans leading-none"
        >
          Engineered for pure network transparency.
        </h1>
        <p
          class="text-base md:text-lg text-body max-w-3xl leading-relaxed mt-2"
        >
          NetSpeed was founded with a singular objective: to provide developers,
          network administrators, and everyday users with an accurate, ads-free,
          and high-fidelity telemetry platform. By deploying concurrent streams
          and measuring real-time latency variance, we expose the true
          limitations of your internet routing.
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* Core Technology Philosophy Grid */}
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 pt-4">
        <div class="vercel-card p-6 flex flex-col gap-3 justify-between">
          <div>
            <span
              class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider text-mute block mb-1"
            >
              Methodology 01
            </span>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink font-sans">
              Zero payload caching
            </h2>
            <p class="text-xs md:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed mt-2">
              Traditional speed test applications fetch static files that can
              easily be cached by local internet service providers (ISPs) or
              content delivery networks (CDNs). NetSpeed leverages Cloudflare's
              edge network to serve non-compressible binary payloads directly
              from the nearest data center, forcing your ISP to handle raw,
              unoptimized data transit.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="vercel-card p-6 flex flex-col gap-3 justify-between">
          <div>
            <span
              class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider text-mute block mb-1"
            >
              Methodology 02
            </span>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink font-sans">
              Concurrent socket piping
            </h2>
            <p class="text-xs md:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed mt-2">
              Using Web Workers, we initiate six concurrent download connections
              and adaptive upload streams. This parallel pipe design stresses
              your connection capacity, allowing us to accurately measure the
              peak saturation performance and load-balanced capabilities of your
              network interface.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="vercel-card p-6 flex flex-col gap-3 justify-between">
          <div>
            <span
              class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider text-mute block mb-1"
            >
              Methodology 03
            </span>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink font-sans">
              Bufferbloat loaded latency
            </h2>
            <p class="text-xs md:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed mt-2">
              A high download speed is useless if your ping spikes to several
              hundred milliseconds when downloading files. We run loaded latency
              tests during both download and upload stages to quantify
              bufferbloat stability and let you know if your router's queueing
              algorithm is failing.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="vercel-card p-6 flex flex-col gap-3 justify-between">
          <div>
            <span
              class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider text-mute block mb-1"
            >
              Methodology 04
            </span>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink font-sans">
              Optimal server selection
            </h2>
            <p class="text-xs md:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed mt-2">
              NetSpeed identifies which Cloudflare edge datacenter is serving
              your request. Cloudflare's Anycast BGP routing automatically
              connects you to the nearest edge based on real-time network
              topology. We display the selected edge and estimated distance for
              transparency, ensuring you know exactly where your measurements
              are being taken.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Corporate stats or details banner */}
      <section class="border-t border-hairline pt-12">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start md:items-center justify-between gap-6 bg-canvas-soft-2 p-8 rounded-lg border border-hairline"
        >
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 max-w-xl">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">
              Looking for our diagnostic details?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-body leading-relaxed">
              We compile detailed network packets, routing distances, and raw
              connection logs for every benchmark run. You can export these
              reports directly from the home screen dashboard in standard
              format.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            href="/"
            class="bg-primary text-on-primary font-medium text-xs rounded-full py-2 px-6 hover:opacity-90 active:scale-95 transition-[opacity,transform] text-center select-none cursor-pointer inline-block whitespace-nowrap shadow-xs"
          >
            Run Speed Test
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
